ure Token Service to fetch a set of session credentials.&#10;@return boolean A value of `false` if no valid values are set, otherwise `true`." ilk="function" line="368" lineend="401" name="__construct" returns="boolean" signature="boolean __construct(string $key = null, string $secret_key = null, string $token = null)"><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="368" name="key" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="368" name="secret_key" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="368" name="token" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Handle session-based authentication for services that support it.&#10;&#10;@param string $key (Optional) Your AWS key, or a session key. If blank, it will look for the &lt;code&gt;AWS_KEY&lt;/code&gt; constant.&#10;@param string $secret_key (Optional) Your AWS secret key, or a session secret key. If blank, it will look for the &lt;code&gt;AWS_SECRET_KEY&lt;/code&gt; constant.&#10;@param string $token (optional) An AWS session token. If blank, a request will be made to the AWS Secure Token Service to fetch a set of session credentials.&#10;@return boolean A value of `false` if no valid values are set, otherwise `true`." ilk="function" line="411" lineend="475" name="session_based_auth" returns="boolean" signature="boolean session_based_auth(string $key = null, string $secret_key = null, string $token = null)"><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="411" name="key" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="411" name="secret_key" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="411" name="token" /><variable citdl="cache_object.response_manager()" line="459" name="session_credentials" /><variable line="456" name="cache_object" /><variable citdl="this.cache_class" line="455" name="cache_class" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="The callback function that is executed  while caching the session credentials.&#10;&#10;